On December 9, 2010, the President signed several laws into effect. These include the "Telework Enhancement Act of 2010," which requires Federal agencies to allow certain employees to work remotely. Another law is the "Help Haiti Act of 2010," which grants permanent resident status to certain Haitian orphans. The "Animal Crush Video Prohibition Act of 2010" prohibits the creation and distribution of obscene videos depicting animals being intentionally killed or harmed. Lastly, the "Copyright Cleanup, Clarification, and Corrections Act of 2010" amends copyright law to promote the use of electronic information by the Copyright Office and make various technical changes.